Posts.Content: Jun 17, 2013 08:59PM sweke wrote: Thank you!  I was diagnosed May 22, double mastectomy May 30, and told today that I have to have chemo because my Oncotype results were itermediate.  I don't think I ever got my head around actually having to get chemo.  And I don't like my 94% survival rate because it looks like it stops after 10 years !!! (although I know it doesn't). Keep coming with real life info like that.  It's very much appreciated!
